{
  "version": "2",
  "templates": [
    {
      "type": 3,
      "title": "Hawser Edge + Bifrost",
      "description": "Dockhand Edge agent tunnelled through a Bifrost WireGuard connection",
      "logo": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/st0o0/bifrost/main/docs/static/img/favicon.png",
      "categories": [
        "Monitoring",
        "Networking"
      ],
      "repository": {
        "url": "https://github.com/st0o0/homelab-catalog",
        "stackfile": "stacks/hawser-edge-bifrost/compose.yml"
      },
      "env": [
        {
          "name": "DOCKHAND_SERVER_URL",
          "label": "Dockhand Server URL (via tunnel, e.g. http://10.13.13.1:9000)",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "TOKEN",
          "label": "Edge Token",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "AGENT_NAME",
          "label": "Agent Name",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL",
          "label": "Heartbeat Interval (seconds)",
          "default": "30"
        },
        {
          "name": "DOCKER_SOCKET",
          "label": "Docker Socket Path",
          "default": "/var/run/docker.sock"
        },
        {
          "name": "STACKS_PATH",
          "label": "Stacks Storage Path (host path or named volume)",
          "default": "hawser-stacks"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PRIVATE_KEY",
          "label": "WireGuard Private Key",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_ADDRESS",
          "label": "Tunnel Address (CIDR)",
          "default": "10.13.13.2/32"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PEER_PUBLIC_KEY",
          "label": "Peer Public Key (central server)",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PEER_ENDPOINT",
          "label": "Peer Endpoint (host:port)",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PEER_ALLOWED_IPS",
          "label": "Peer Allowed IPs",
          "default": "10.13.13.0/24"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PEER_PRESHARED_KEY",
          "label": "Peer Preshared Key (optional)",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "TZ",
          "label": "Timezone",
          "default": "Europe/Berlin"
        }
      ],
      "note": "Deploys 2 containers: hawser-bifrost (WireGuard, NET_ADMIN) and hawser-edge (network_mode: service:bifrost). All Dockhand traffic flows through the WireGuard tunnel — nothing exposed on the public network. Set DOCKHAND_SERVER_URL to the Dockhand instance's tunnel IP (e.g. http://10.13.13.1:9000)."
    },
    {
      "type": 3,
      "title": "Hawser (Edge)",
      "description": "Dockhand Edge agent — outbound WebSocket, no inbound ports needed",
      "categories": [
        "Monitoring"
      ],
      "repository": {
        "url": "https://github.com/st0o0/homelab-catalog",
        "stackfile": "stacks/hawser-edge/compose.yml"
      },
      "env": [
        {
          "name": "DOCKHAND_SERVER_URL",
          "label": "Dockhand Server URL (e.g. https://dockhand.example.com)",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "TOKEN",
          "label": "Edge Token",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "AGENT_NAME",
          "label": "Agent Name",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL",
          "label": "Heartbeat Interval (seconds)",
          "default": "30"
        },
        {
          "name": "DOCKER_SOCKET",
          "label": "Docker Socket Path",
          "default": "/var/run/docker.sock"
        },
        {
          "name": "STACKS_PATH",
          "label": "Stacks Storage Path (host path or named volume)",
          "default": "hawser-stacks"
        },
        {
          "name": "TZ",
          "label": "Timezone",
          "default": "Europe/Berlin"
        }
      ],
      "note": "Deploys Hawser in Edge mode: initiates an outbound WebSocket connection to the central Dockhand server. No inbound ports required — works behind NAT and firewalls."
    },
    {
      "type": 3,
      "title": "Hawser",
      "description": "Dockhand agent for managing remote Docker environments",
      "categories": [
        "Monitoring"
      ],
      "repository": {
        "url": "https://github.com/st0o0/homelab-catalog",
        "stackfile": "stacks/hawser/compose.yml"
      },
      "env": [
        {
          "name": "TOKEN",
          "label": "Agent Token (required)",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "AGENT_NAME",
          "label": "Agent Name",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "HAWSER_PORT",
          "label": "Published Port",
          "default": "2376"
        },
        {
          "name": "DOCKER_SOCKET",
          "label": "Docker Socket Path",
          "default": "/var/run/docker.sock"
        },
        {
          "name": "STACKS_PATH",
          "label": "Stacks Storage Path (host path or named volume)",
          "default": "hawser-stacks"
        },
        {
          "name": "TZ",
          "label": "Timezone",
          "default": "Europe/Berlin"
        }
      ],
      "note": "Deploys Hawser in standard mode. Port 2376 must be reachable from the central Dockhand server. A TOKEN is required when the port is exposed on a non-loopback address."
    },
    {
      "type": 3,
      "title": "Bifrost",
      "description": "WireGuard tunnel sidecar with automatic DDNS re-resolution, reconnect, and liveness probes",
      "logo": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/st0o0/bifrost/main/docs/static/img/favicon.png",
      "categories": [
        "Networking"
      ],
      "repository": {
        "url": "https://github.com/st0o0/homelab-catalog",
        "stackfile": "stacks/bifrost/compose.yml"
      },
      "env": [
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PRIVATE_KEY",
          "label": "WireGuard Private Key",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_ADDRESS",
          "label": "Tunnel Address (CIDR)",
          "default": "10.13.13.2/32"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_LISTEN_PORT",
          "label": "Listen Port",
          "default": "0"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_MTU",
          "label": "MTU",
          "default": "1420"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PEER_PUBLIC_KEY",
          "label": "Peer Public Key",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PEER_PRESHARED_KEY",
          "label": "Peer Preshared Key (optional)",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PEER_ENDPOINT",
          "label": "Peer Endpoint (host:port)",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PEER_ALLOWED_IPS",
          "label": "Peer Allowed IPs",
          "default": "0.0.0.0/0"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PEER_KEEPALIVE",
          "label": "Persistent Keepalive (seconds)",
          "default": "25"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_INTERFACE",
          "label": "Interface Name",
          "default": "wg0"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_RESOLVE",
          "label": "DDNS Re-Resolution",
          "default": "on"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_RECONNECT",
          "label": "Auto Reconnect",
          "default": "on"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_HEALTHCHECK",
          "label": "Healthcheck",
          "default": "on"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PROBE",
          "label": "Liveness Probe",
          "default": "off"
        },
        {
          "name": "EXPOSED_PORT",
          "label": "Exposed Port",
          "default": "8200"
        }
      ],
      "note": "Deploys 1 container with NET_ADMIN capability. Uses the kernel WireGuard module (Linux 5.6+). If your host lacks the module, add /dev/net/tun as a device for the built-in userspace fallback. Services using the tunnel connect via network_mode: service:bifrost."
    },
    {
      "type": 3,
      "title": "Observability Agent",
      "description": "Alloy collector for remote servers shipping metrics and logs to the central stack through a Bifrost WireGuard tunnel",
      "logo": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/st0o0/bifrost/main/docs/static/img/favicon.png",
      "categories": [
        "Observability",
        "Monitoring"
      ],
      "repository": {
        "url": "https://github.com/st0o0/homelab-catalog",
        "stackfile": "stacks/observability-agent/compose.yml"
      },
      "env": [
        {
          "name": "HOST_HOSTNAME",
          "label": "Host Label (unique per server)",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "SCRAPE_INTERVAL",
          "label": "Metrics Scrape Interval",
          "default": "30s"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PRIVATE_KEY",
          "label": "WireGuard Private Key",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_ADDRESS",
          "label": "Tunnel Address (CIDR)",
          "default": "10.13.13.2/32"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PEER_PUBLIC_KEY",
          "label": "Peer Public Key (central server)",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PEER_ENDPOINT",
          "label": "Peer Endpoint (host:port)",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PEER_ALLOWED_IPS",
          "label": "Peer Allowed IPs",
          "default": "10.13.13.0/24"
        },
        {
          "name": "BIFROST_PEER_PRESHARED_KEY",
          "label": "Peer Preshared Key (optional)",
          "default": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "REMOTE_WRITE_URL",
          "label": "VictoriaMetrics Remote Write URL",
          "default": "http://10.13.13.1:8428/api/v1/write"
        },
        {
          "name": "LOGS_PUSH_URL",
          "label": "VictoriaLogs Push URL",
          "default": "http://10.13.13.1:9428/insert/loki/api/v1/push"
        }
      ],
      "note": "Deploys 2 containers: obs-agent-bifrost (WireGuard, NET_ADMIN) and obs-agent-alloy (network_mode: service:bifrost). Alloy mounts /var/log, /proc, /sys, / (read-only) and the docker socket. Set VM_BIND_IP/VLOGS_BIND_IP on the central Observability stack to its WireGuard IP. See stacks/observability-agent/README.md."
    },
    {
